// Weather (SEASONS_WEATHER Subsystem 4) — the single data source. Loaded by EnvironmentService.
//
// Two halves in one file:
//   • types[]  — the LABELLED weather states the rest of the game reads via `weather.type`: each a
//                leaf of effects + visuals ("what does `storm` feel/look like").
//   • the chains (precip / wind / grid …) — when each type is active. Weather is TWO independent
//                Markov chains whose product DERIVES the displayed type:
//                  PRECIP axis (wet) : dry → drizzle → rain → heavy_rain   (+ snow / fog / heat_wave)
//                  WIND   axis       : calm → breezy → windy → gale
//                They evolve separately, so a dry gale, a calm shower, and a windy rain all arise
//                naturally — a windy day never depends on it raining. `storm`/`blizzard` live ONLY in
//                the bottom-right corner (heavy precip AND a gale at once), gated by BOTH chains'
//                weights, so wind can never force a storm on its own.
//
//   default — the starting / fallback weather id (also the dry-calm derivation).
//
//   types[] fields:
//     overlay       — UI animation the WeatherCanvas draws:
//                     "none" | "rain" | "snow" | "fog" | "leaves" | "dust" | "snowdust". Visual only.
//     particleColor — [r,g,b] 0–255 tint for "leaves"/"dust" particles (green spring vs red autumn).
//     windStrength  — inherent windiness 0–1; drives the overlay slant (combined with ambient wind).
//                     Default 0.2 (0.6 if "heavy").
//     sightMul      — environmental sight multiplier 0–1 (1 = clear); fog/storm shorten detection
//                     range for BOTH pawns and mobs (folds into effectiveVisionRange). Default 1.
//     panelSaturation — side-panel colour saturation while active (1 = normal, <1 = washed-out).
//     heavy         — harder wind / slant + longer streaks on the overlay.
//     fallSpeed     — overlay particle fall speed px/sec. Default 680 rain / 80 snow.
//     density       — overlay particle count per megapixel (before intensity/zoom). Default 160/80.
//     intensity     — 0–1; drives overlay opacity AND (× density) particle count.
//     tempDelta     — °C added to effective temperature (cold/heat exposure). Windy cold = windchill;
//                     summer wind is a small negative = cooling relief in the heat.
//     fatigueMul / hungerMul — multipliers on those need rates.
//     moveCostMul   — movement-cost multiplier (gameplay hook).
//     mood          — MOOD-REWORK: a STANDING mood-target offset in points (+ pleasant, − miserable),
//                     summed into each pawn's mood target while this weather holds (a roof softens a
//                     negative one). NOT a per-second drift — mood eases toward the target.
//     moistureBonus — added to tile wetness % while active (soaks pawns); negative dries (heat wave).
//     tint          — normalised RGB multiplied into the ambient tint.
//     severity      — chronicle severity on onset: "info" | "warning".
{
  "default": "clear",
  "types"  : [
    {
      "id"           : "clear",
      "label"        : "Clear skies",
      "overlay"      : "none",
      "windStrength" : 0.1,
